    <note>Tian(1) Xi [1615] He was buried in Sizhou, Linhuai county and may have moved there. However, his great grandson, Yan [21612], who was Yanshi county magistrate (Henan Fu), requested a beiyin from Sima(1) Guang [1488] in ca. 1070. Yan had the same generational name as Hui [21613], a Jiading jinshi in ca. 1079, which suggests that the family, or at least some family members, remained in Sichuan. Du Dagui, 'zhong,' 2.3b-4a (beiyin); Fan Zhongyan, WJ, 12.5a-7b; XCB, 22.6b; SS, 293.1a; SHY:SH, 49.5b-6a. CBD, 1, 461-2.</note>
